Just because you are not overweight doesn't mean you are fit or healthy. Besides it's a fucking commercial. Plenty of women including myself have asked for health and fitness related gifts.  Even if not why would you immediately assume the worst about the givers intentions or thoughts? That fitness is seen in such a negative light when someone is really sharing something that helps keep you healthy or an activity that they themselves enjoy and want to share with you shows that it's more needed than ever.
